# Guardyn Licensing

Copyright 2025 Guardyn Team

This project uses a hybrid open-core licensing model.

---

## Community Edition Components (Apache License 2.0)

The core components of Guardyn, including the client applications and core server functionalities, are licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0. A full copy of this license can be found in the `LICENSE` file.

This includes, but is not limited to:

- Client Applications (iOS, Android, Desktop, Web)
- Core Backend Services (Authentication, Messaging, Presence, etc.)
- Cryptographic Libraries

---

## Enterprise Edition Components (Business Source License 1.1)

Advanced features designed for enterprise use are licensed under the Business Source License 1.1 (BSL). This code is source-available and will convert to the GNU Affero General Public License v3.0 (AGPLv3) after a period of 4 years from its release date.

These features are available under a commercial license for production use cases that exceed the "Additional Use Grant" or for providing a competing hosted service.

Enterprise features include:

- LDAP/SAML/SSO Integration
- Administrative Console
- Compliance and Audit Logging
- Advanced Security and Retention Policies

---

## Managed Cloud Service (Proprietary)

The Guardyn Cloud is a fully managed, proprietary SaaS offering. The code and infrastructure specific to the operation of Guardyn Cloud are not open source.

---

For more details on licensing, please contact <legal@guardyn.io>.
